    "body": "<!-- markdownlint-disable -->\n\n## Purpose\nTune the num_splits heuristic for CUTLASS_MLA to achieve some speedup now that #26026 has fixed the hang. Based on experiments performed using the tools introduced in #26835, this is the optimal num_splits policy:\n\n<img width=\"3331\" height=\"2363\" alt=\"numsplits_heatmap\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c2898b4c-2ff2-4965-a760-9bc71446e945\" />\n\nFollowing the optimal policy would yield this speedup:\n\n<img width=\"3331\" height=\"2363\" alt=\"numsplits_speedup\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/06f76c49-d4cf-4817-9bc0-964f919ab0e7\" />\n\nAs a simpler alternative, we implement a heuristic yielding the following policy:\n\n<img width=\"3335\" height=\"2364\" alt=\"numsplits_policy_batch-based_improved\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f5834e32-d0b8-48ca-afd2-f06ff508e694\" />\n\nThis results in the following speedup:\n\n<img width=\"3331\" height=\"2364\" alt=\"numsplits_speedup_batch-based_improved\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/71af1582-09ac-4f45-baeb-799b7002050c\" />\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
